<TITLE> Arrest, vandalism prevent SQ Chy rally </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 2 (bdnews24.com)  A Chittagong rally where the senior BNP leader Salahuddin Quader Chowdhury was due to attend was cancelled when one of its organisers was arrested and its stage was vandalised. Local BNP leaders accuse AL activists and the police of working hand in hand to prevent the meeting which was due to have taken take place on Sunday at Gachhbaria College intersection of Chandanaish upazila in Chittagong The Awami League activists had earlier announced that they would prevent the BNP leader from attending the rally accusing him of playing a controversial role during the Liberation War in 1971. Police, on Saturday night, arrested Abul Hashem Razu, the general secretary of the upazila, a noted follower of Salahuddin, and an organiser of the meeting. Chandanaish police chief Nur Mohammad told bdnews24.com that Razu was arrested in a fraud case. He also said that BNP activists had not taken necessary permission from the police before the meeting. Concerning the allegation of vandalism, the police officer said that they had not received any information. BNP president of Chandanaish, Abu Taher Chowdhury told bdnews24.com, "AL activists and the police have joined hands to arrest Razu and prevent the rally." However, the Awami League general secretary of Chandanaish upazila, Wahiduzzaman claimed to bdnews24.com that AL activists were not involved in vandalising BNP archways, claiming that it was a consequence of BNP's internal feud. "We only said that we would hold a rally demanding trial of war criminals," the AL leader said. Addtional police have been deployed where the street rally was to take place to avert any untoward incident, Mohammad said. With the cancellation of the rally, SQ Chowdhury went directly to Bandarban to join a Juba Dal convention. bdne
